''' Chien de Jean de Nivelle''' (the dog of Jean de Nivelle) is an animal or a man who does not want to obey when called, as in the expression ''Here comes the dog of Jean de Nivelle, it flees when it is called''. The Origins of the expression are unknown. It is thought that this Jean de Nivelle refused to help his father, [[Jean de Montmorency]], to support [[Louis XI of France|Louis XI]] in the war against the [[duke of Burgundy]]. Furious, his father disinherited him and Jean de Nivelle fleed to [[Flanders]] without awaiting other troubles. 

